{
  "name": "RPlog_A_Ray_of_Hope",
  "title": "A Ray of Hope",
  "summary": "Disguised as a filthy beggar in a Tatooine trading square, the Corellian Paul Nighman -- injured, his left arm in a sling -- waits for the Horansi fixer Xanthe, who finds him beneath the rags and leads him back to her hidden quarters. After bathing and shaving, Paul lays out his need: undetectable infrared lenses that will let him see in the dark without affecting his vision in the light, part of a plan to break into the sanctum of Ullo the Hutt and steal something the crime lord prizes. Xanthe, wary of crossing a dangerous and lucrative client yet eager to see Ullo humbled, agrees to craft the rare optics in three days and to help him smuggle items off a quarantined ship and find passage off-world, asking only the retrieval of whatever he is after as part of her payment. She warns him that Ullo has been in a black mood for weeks and urges caution; then, sensing his fear and exhaustion, she eases his tension with a massage, coaching him to visualize his infiltration and escape until he finally relaxes, safe for the moment in the care of an old, dangerous friend.",
